subSubSection.paragraph:
Medium-large-sized shells (SL max.: 
82.8 mm
). Spire whorls of medium height, conical to convex in outline in early spire whorls, coeloconoid in late spire whorls. Early spire whorls conical, convex, slightly elevated. Middle spire whorls convex, with straight to convex sutural ramp. Last two to three whorls widened, with straight or inflated, deep suture. Absence of ornamentation along the sutural ramp. Subsutural flexure deep to very deep, rarely moderately deep, usually moderately to rarely strongly curved, strongly asymmetrical (
Fig. 40O
). Shoulder smooth, with weak angulation near external part of sutural ramp, more angulated on last whorl. Aperture straight, relatively narrow. Fasciole carved by growth lines. Last whorl straight conical.
